4A::Interfacing of Inbuilt LED (connected to GPIO1 for ESP-01 or GPIO2
for ESP-01S) to ESP01/ESP01S/ESP8266 module and program in Em-
bedded C to blink a LED for every 1 second delay
Algorithm
1. Start
2. Configure port (connected to GPIO1 for ESP-01 or GPIO2 for ESP-01S) (as
inbuilt LED) pin as output pin where LEDs are connected.
3. Send logic 1 to port pin.
4. Give a delay of 1 second.
5. Send logic 0 to port pin.
6. Give a delay of 1 second.
7. Go to step 2
8. Stop

// the setup function runs once when you press reset or power the board
void setup() {
  // initialize digital pin LED_BUILTIN as an output.
  pinMode(LED_BUILTIN, OUTPUT);
}

// the loop function runs over and over again forever
void loop() {
  digitalWrite(LED_BUILTIN, HIGH);  // turn the LED on (HIGH is the voltage level)
  delay(1000);                      // wait for a second
  digitalWrite(LED_BUILTIN, LOW);   // turn the LED off by making the voltage LOW
  delay(1000);                      // wait for a second
}


4B:: Interfacing of Relay module to ESP01 and controlling the applica-
tions connected to Relay through GPIO0 port pin*/

Algorithm
1. Start
2. Configure port GPIO0 pin as output pin where Relay are connected.
3. Send logic 0 to port pin (Turn ON Relay as it is negative triggered relay).
4. Give a delay of 1 second.
5. Send logic 1 to port pin.(To turn OFF relay)
6. Give a delay of 1 second.
7. Go to step 2
8. Stop


#define RELAY_PIN 0   // GPIO0 of ESP-01

void setup() {
  pinMode(RELAY_PIN, OUTPUT);
  digitalWrite(RELAY_PIN, HIGH); // Keep relay OFF initially
}

void loop() {
 
  digitalWrite(RELAY_PIN, LOW);   // Active LOW for most relay modules
  delay(5000); // ON for 5 seconds
  digitalWrite(RELAY_PIN, HIGH);
  delay(5000); // OFF for 5 seconds
}


4C:: Blynk
Algorithm
1. Start
2. Create dashboard on Desktop/Laptop and mobile using BLYNK app.
3. Include necessary header files required for initialization of ESP WiFi module.
4. Define necessary credentials of wifi name and password
5. Include token id generated from Blynk
6. Initialize direction of respective port pin as a output.
7. Initialize virtual pin in blynk V0
8. Capture the information capture through virtual pin and transfer it to respec-
tive port pin for controlling.
9. Run Blynk in forever loop
10. Stop
